Packages

library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(sp)
library(fuzzyjoin)
library(getarc)
library(janitor)
library(vroom)
library(fs)
library(gridExtra)
temps <-
  fs::dir_ls("project_data/", regexp = "daily*") %>%
  vroom::vroom() %>% 
  janitor::clean_names()
head(temps)

There are some suspect values in the data such as temperatures below -50 and years before 1995. I’m going to fix them with an assumption or convert them to missing values.

set.seed(1)
year_hist <- 
  temps %>%
  slice_sample(n = 10000) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year)) +
  geom_histogram() + 
  labs(title = "Year")

temp_hist <- 
  temps %>%
  slice_sample(n = 10000) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = avg_temperature)) +
  geom_histogram() + 
  labs(title = "Avg Temp")

grid.arrange(year_hist, temp_hist)

temps <- 
    temps %>% 
    mutate(day = if_else(day < 1, 1, day), 
            year = if_else(year < 1995, NA_real_, year), 
            avg_temperature = if_else(avg_temperature < -50, NA_real_, avg_temperature)
            )

City Locations

ep_esri_city_points <- 
"https://services.arcgis.com/P3ePLMYs2RVChkJx/arcgis/rest/services/World_Cities/FeatureServer/0"

city_points <- query_layer(endpoint = ep_esri_city_points) %>% clean_names()

rmarkdown::paged_table(city_points)

Matching up the City temps with their location

Many of the cities in the dataset don’t have a match in the ESRI data.

temps %>% 
  select(city) %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  anti_join(city_points, by = c("city" = "city_name"))
